  "prompt": "When will I be able to sign up by means other than Facebook?",
  "response": "I understand you'd like to sign up for a service using a method other than Facebook. However, to provide a more accurate answer, I would need to know which specific platform or service you're referring to. \n\nIn general, many platforms initially offer Facebook (or other social media) sign-up options for convenience but also support alternative methods such as:\n\n1. **Email Registration:** Creating an account using your email address.\n2. **Phone Number:** Signing up with your mobile number.\n3. **Other Social Accounts:** Using Google, Apple, or other social media accounts.\n4. **Username and Password:** Setting up a traditional account with a unique username and password.\n\nIf the service currently only supports Facebook sign-up, here are some steps you can take:\n\n1. **Check the FAQ or Help Center:** Often, platforms provide information about upcoming features or alternative sign-up methods in their support sections.\n2. **Contact Support:** Reach out directly to the platform's customer service or support team to inquire about alternative registration options and any planned updates.\n3. **Stay Updated:** Follow the platform's official social media channels or newsletters, as they may announce new sign-up methods through these channels.\n\nIf you provide more details about the specific service you're referring to, I can offer more targeted assistance!",
